data.name: Loc_UsePriorizedIcons_Description
data.value: This option checked will force a set of status icons to be priorized over job icons, if you enabled job icons. When disabled, only the disconnected status icon is priorized.

data.name: Loc_DefaultPluginDataTemplate_Basic_Description
data.value: Same as Empty, but includes a very basic pre-configuration for formatting and coloring. Can also be used if you want to make your own configuration but want basic formatting.

data.name: Loc_DefaultPluginDataTemplate_Description
data.value:
Here you can choose the template for all the settings below. The template is used as basic set of properties. Every change you are making is what get saved. But all options from this template will not be saved. This helps you by not needing to overwrite so much properties - or by doing your completely own configuration without a template.
Warning: Changing this can cause properties to be resetted. You may loose a part of your configuration. After you changed this, ensure everything is setted up how you like it.

data.name: Loc_DefaultPluginDataTemplate_Full_Description
data.value: Show the job tag with color and also color the player name element.

data.name: Loc_DefaultPluginDataTemplate_None_Description
data.value: No single configuration made. This is a completely empty template. Use this if you want to to have every option under your control or just want to make only a few configurations.

data.name: Loc_DefaultPluginDataTemplate_Simple_Description
data.value: Shows the job tag with color and the role icon by replacing the title.

data.name: Loc_DeadPlayerHandling_GrayOut_Description
data.value: Apply any tag but gray out the nameplate.

data.name: Loc_DeadPlayerHandling_Ignore_Description
data.value: Don't process dead players and don't apply any tag for.

data.name: Loc_DeadPlayerHandling_Include_Description
data.value: Handle dead players as they are alive. No difference between dead and alive players.

data.name: Loc_MoveStatusIconToNameplateTextIfPossible
data.value: Move Status Icon to Nameplate text if possible

data.name: Loc_MoveStatusIconToNameplateTextIfPossible_Description
data.value: If the current status icon is available as Font Icon then move it to the Player Name text in the Nameplate, so there is place for another icon to use, e.g. the job icon.

data.name: Loc_TargetChatTypesIncludeUndefined_Description
data.value: When enabled the Tag will apply to all Chat messages that has not a defined type. This case can happen either if the Game updates and the Enumeration of all Chat Types gets invalid due to shifted values, or plugins creates a custom chat type for whatever reason.
